{"type":"text","timestamp":1780372896821,"sessionID":"ses_179821a7fffeliBzI3TOZnRjZf","part":{"id":"prt_e867e6a27001ZV06NILFGQe3jK","messageID":"msg_e867e5478001iXymuwFIE4RAhB","sessionID":"ses_179821a7fffeliBzI3TOZnRjZf","type":"text","text":"I’m focusing iteration #5 on gold-to-RESOURCE_MAP reconciliation, because iteration #4 already bounded the asset-scoring seam and explicitly left SD-001/CS-001 recall misses as the next highest-value lever.","time":{"start":1780372892199,"end":1780372896818},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b91e6a34f951fa7016a1e559c2d1c81919e1dfbf24a9bc25f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780372896897,"sessionID":"ses_179821a7fffeliBzI3TOZnRjZf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Q16ROiC8CzTvKgqUiYoAdjg2","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--cross-skill-composition/018-webflow-plus-motion-dev.md","offset":1,"limit":90},"error":"File not found: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/02--cross-skill-composition/018-webflow-plus-motion-dev.md","time":{"start":1780372896877,"end":1780372896886}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b91e6a34f951fa7016a1e55a0c6f0819182b60ecd3b4e1048"}},"id":"prt_e867e7c6b001MFqLX5BCpB3RMN","sessionID":"ses_179821a7fffeliBzI3TOZnRjZf","messageID":"msg_e867e5478001iXymuwFIE4RAhB"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780372896897,"sessionID":"ses_179821a7fffeliBzI3TOZnRjZf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_HRBfmsTMGXMC0PA2xIuyrccO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/01--surface-detection/001-webflow-detection.md","offset":1,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/01--surface-detection/001-webflow-detection.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"SD-001: WEBFLOW Surface Detection\"\n3: description: \"Verify sk-code routes vanilla-JS / animation-library prompts to the WEBFLOW surface and loads the webflow/* reference and asset trees.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # SD-001: WEBFLOW Surface Detection\n7: \n8: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n9: \n10: This scenario verifies that sk-code's smart router correctly identifies WEBFLOW as the active code surface when the prompt references vanilla-JS animation libraries (motion.dev, GSAP, Lenis, HLS, Swiper, FilePond) or marker file paths (`src/2_javascript/`, `*.webflow.js`, `wrangler.toml`).\n11: \n12: WEBFLOW is the frontend HTML/CSS/JS surface for Webflow / vanilla-animation projects. When detected, sk-code MUST load `references/webflow/*` and `assets/webflow/*` and SHOULD NOT load any `references/opencode/*` resources.\n13: \n14: Detection markers are defined verbatim in `references/stack_detection.md:30-37`.\n15: \n16: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n17: \n18: **Realistic user request**: A frontend developer working on a Webflow site asks the AI to add smooth-scroll behavior using the Lenis library, gated behind an IntersectionObserver so it only initializes once the user scrolls into the hero section.\n19: \n20: **Exact prompt**:\n21: ```\n22: Add Lenis smooth-scroll to src/2_javascript/scroll.js, gated by IntersectionObserver when the hero becomes visible.\n23: ```\n24: \n25: **Expected detection**:\n26: - Surface: `WEBFLOW`\n27: - Triggering markers: `src/2_javascript/` (path marker) AND `Lenis` (library marker) → either alone is sufficient per `code_surface_detection.md:30-37`.\n28: \n29: **Expected references loaded** (exact relative paths under `.opencode/skills/sk-code/`):\n30: - `references/stack_detection.md` (always loaded for router decision)\n31: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n32: - `references/smart_routing.md`\n33: - `references/phase_detection.md`\n34: - `references/universal/code_quality_standards.md`\n35: - `references/webflow/implementation/webflow_patterns.md`\n36: - `references/webflow/implementation/animation_workflows.md`\n37: - `references/webflow/implementation/observer_patterns.md`\n38: - `references/webflow/javascript/quality_standards.md`\n39: - `references/webflow/javascript/style_guide.md`\n40: - `references/webflow/css/style_guide.md`\n41: - `references/webflow/shared/cross_language_rules.md`\n42: \n43: **Expected assets loaded**:\n44: - `assets/webflow/checklists/code_quality_checklist.md`\n45: - `assets/webflow/patterns/interaction_gate_patterns.js` (when intent is implementation gating)\n46: \n47: **Expected NOT loaded**: any `references/opencode/*` or `assets/opencode/*` (would indicate misrouting).\n48: \n49: **Expected agent dispatch**: `@code` (LEAF) for the actual edit, dispatched ONLY by `@orchestrate`. If the user prompt is invoked directly without orchestration, the AI may apply the change inline using sk-code guidance without dispatching @code.\n50: \n51: **Desired user-visible outcome**: The AI applies the edit to `src/2_javascript/scroll.js`, citing webflow-specific patterns (IntersectionObserver gate from `assets/webflow/patterns/interaction_gate_patterns.js`) and confirming the modification with a Lenis initializer + observer fence.\n52: \n53: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n54: \n55: ### Preconditions\n56: \n57: 1. `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` is at HEAD-of-main.\n58: 2. `references/stack_detection.md:30-37` contains the WEBFLOW marker block (verify with `head -40 .opencode/skills/sk-code/references/stack_detection.md`).\n59: 3. Sandbox: create `/tmp/skc-SD001-sandbox/src/2_javascript/scroll.js` with placeholder content (the AI doesn't need to actually write — we're testing routing).\n60: 4. Skill advisor binary callable: `python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py --help` exits 0.\n61: \n62: ### Exact Command Sequence\n63: \n64: 1. **Skill advisor probe**:\n65:    ```\n66:    bash: python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py \"Add Lenis smooth-scroll to src/2_javascript/scroll.js, gated by IntersectionObserver when the hero becomes visible.\" --threshold 0.8 > /tmp/skc-SD001-advisor.txt\n67:    ```\n68: 2. **Verify advisor result**: top-1 == `sk-code`, score ≥ 0.80.\n69: 3. **Invoke sk-code** in the orchestrator runtime by feeding the same prompt.\n70: 4. **Capture sk-code output**: which surface did it report? Which references did it list as loaded?\n71: 5. **Persist evidence**: save the AI's response (including its surface-detection log line and its loaded-refs list) to `/tmp/skc-SD001-loaded-refs.txt`.\n72: \n73: ### Expected Signals (per step)\n74: \n75: | Step | Signal |\n76: |---|---|\n77: | 1 | Advisor returns JSON with `top_skill: \"sk-code\"`, `score: ≥ 0.80`. |\n78: | 2 | Pass — proceed. |\n79: | 3 | sk-code SKILL.md is loaded; the AI runs the smart router pseudocode and emits `SURFACE: WEBFLOW`. |\n80: | 4 | The AI lists `references/webflow/implementation/*` as loaded; lists `assets/webflow/checklists/code_quality_checklist.md` as loaded; does NOT list any `references/opencode/*`. |\n81: | 5 | Evidence file contains all of the above. |\n82: \n83: ### Pass/Fail Criteria\n84: \n85: - **PASS** iff:\n86:   - Advisor wins sk-code at score ≥ 0.80.\n87:   - sk-code reports surface == WEBFLOW.\n88:   - Loaded references include at least 3 paths under `references/webflow/implementation/`.\n89:   - Loaded references DO NOT include any `references/opencode/`.\n90: - **PARTIAL** iff:\n\n(Showing lines 1-90 of 116. Use offset=91 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"SD-001: WEBFLOW Surface Detection\"\ndescription: \"Verify sk-code routes vanilla-JS / animation-library prompts to the WEBFLOW surface and loads the webflow/* reference and asset trees.\"\n---\n\n# SD-001: WEBFLOW Surface Detection\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis scenario verifies that sk-code's smart router correctly identifies WEBFLOW as the active code surface when the prompt references vanilla-JS animation libraries (motion.dev, GSAP, Lenis, HLS, Swiper, FilePond) or marker file paths (`src/2_javascript/`, `*.webflow.js`, `wrangler.toml`).\n\nWEBFLOW is the frontend HTML/CSS/JS surface for Webflow / vanilla-animation projects. When detected, sk-code MUST load `references/webflow/*` and `assets/webflow/*` and SHOULD NOT load any `references/opencode/*` resources.\n\nDetection markers are defined verbatim in `references/stack_detection.md:30-37`.\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n**Realistic user request**: A frontend developer working on a Webflow site asks the AI to add smooth-scroll behavior using the Lenis library, gated behind an IntersectionObserver so it only initializes once the user scrolls into the hero section.\n\n**Exact prompt**:","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/01--surface-detection/001-webflow-detection.md","time":{"start":1780372896873,"end":1780372896892}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b91e6a34f951fa7016a1e55a0c6e881919713d96b071a5087"}},"id":"prt_e867e7c5d001KnzMIuF3BuigJt","sessionID":"ses_179821a7fffeliBzI3TOZnRjZf","messageID":"msg_e867e5478001iXymuwFIE4RAhB"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780372896897,"sessionID":"ses_179821a7fffeliBzI3TOZnRjZf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_zrzPvnVtwhXyUPhdxAHzMCEm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/011-sk-code-routing-efficiency-remediation/research/research.md","offset":1,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/011-sk-code-routing-efficiency-remediation/research/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research — sk-code Routing-Efficiency & Usefulness Remediation\n2: \n3: > Synthesized from 3 native-Opus `@deep-research` iterations (converged at the planned stop). Source iterations: `iterations/iteration-00{1,2,3}.md`. Canonical findings ledger: `deltas/iter-00{1,2,3}.jsonl`.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Question\n6: \n7: How can `sk-code` load a tighter, task-appropriate resource slice that cuts **D3 over-routing** (live 42; routed ~16-20 vs gold ~5-8) and lifts **D4 routine-task usefulness** (≈49, task-dependent) **without regressing D1 routing or D2 discovery**?\n8: \n9: ## 2. Convergence Report\n10: \n11: | Iteration | Focus | newInfoRatio | Outcome |\n12: |---|---|---|---|\n13: | 1 | Root cause + structural H1/H2 | 0.70 | Root cause isolated; H1 = primary structural fix |\n14: | 2 | Dynamic H3/H4 + quantified frontier | 0.62 | H3 folds into H4; D2 was never 1.0; frontier quantified |\n15: | 3 | Synthesis + recommendation + guard | 0.18 | Ranked deliverable; converged |\n16: \n17: Stop reason: **converged at the planned iteration 3** (all 4 hypotheses resolved, all 4 REQs answered).\n18: \n19: ## 3. Root Cause (verified)\n20: \n21: The `RESOURCE_MAP` keys on **intent only**; each intent value is a flat list that **unions Webflow + Motion.dev + OpenCode + universal** resources under one key. The §11 preamble documents this as intentional lossiness (\"Surface is flattened … a replay that sees prompt text alone will over-route relative to a single surface\"). The waste is therefore the **cross-surface half of every union**, concentrated in the 20-path `IMPLEMENTATION` and 21-path `LANGUAGE_STANDARDS` keys — not a routing-accuracy defect (surface detection is correct on 3/3 live scenarios, `surfaceMatch=true`).\n22: \n23: D4 localizes the harm mechanistically: the same union that *helps* the domain-pattern task (CS-001 0.88 vs 0.78) *hurts* the routine task (LS-001 0.82 vs 0.95). The differential is the cross-surface contamination, not raw volume.\n24: \n25: ## 4. Quantified Frontier (recovered gold sets)\n26: \n27: | Scenario | Surface | Gold refs | Routed | Wasted | D3 | D2 (baseline) |\n28: |---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n29: | LS-001 | OPENCODE | 5 | 16 | 11 | 0.312 | **1.0** |\n30: | SD-001 | WEBFLOW | ~11 | 20 | 12 | 0.40 | **0.727** |\n31: | CS-001 | WEBFLOW+Motion | ~11 | 16 | 10 | 0.375 | **0.60** |\n32: \n33: **Load-bearing fact:** D2 recall was **never 1.0** on SD-001/CS-001 — the union over-routes *and* under-recalls simultaneously. So the regression guard floor is the **measured baseline**, not 1.0. Also: `assets/*` paths are parsed (`expectedAssets`) but **never merged into scored gold**, so every routed `assets/*` counts as waste regardless of real usefulness (a measurement seam, not a routing defect).\n34: \n35: ## 5. Ranked Approaches\n36: \n37: | Rank | Approach | D3↓ | D1/D2 safe? | Cost/risk |\n38: |---|---|---|---|---|\n39: | **1** | **H1 — surface-nested RESOURCE_MAP** | Highest (removes cross-surface half) | D1 safe; D2 safe **only with the cross-surface overlay** | Low — re-keys an already-reliable signal |\n40: | **2** | **H4 — intra-surface intent-score ranking** (references only, no count cap; absorbs H3) | Medium (only dynamic lever that moves *scored* D3) | Safe only if intra-surface + references-only | Low-med |\n41: | 3 | H2 — phase-gating | Low (within-surface, wrong-phase only) | D2 risk (implementation trio is a hard contract) | Med-high (weakest signal; projection drops the +5 phase boost) |\n42: | — | H3 — lazy/progressive | None independently (no replay trigger; cost invisible to metric) | — | Do **not** build separately |\n43: \n44: ## 6. Recommendation (build-ready)\n45: \n46: **Primary: H1 surface-nested map + a MANDATORY full, unranked cross-surface overlay. Complementary: H4 intra-surface intent-score ranking. Do not build H3 separately. Defer H2.**\n47: \n48: Composition at route time (fixed order):\n49: \n50: ```text\n51: route(prompt, surface, crossSurface):\n52:   1. base    = DEFAULT_RESOURCE                                   # surface-agnostic preamble, always loaded\n53:   2. intents = selectIntents(scoreIntents(prompt))                # H4 lever lives here\n54:   3. primary = ∪ RESOURCE_MAP[surface][intent]                    # H1: detected surface slice ONLY\n55:              + ∪ RESOURCE_MAP[\"UNIVERSAL\"][intent]                # shared refs stay in a UNIVERSAL tier (no duplication)\n56:   4. overlay = if crossSurface: ∪ RESOURCE_MAP[secondarySurface][intent]   # FULL, UNRANKED\n57:              + if MOTION_DEV intent: MOTION_DEV_OVERLAY           # Motion.dev = peer category, additive\n58:   5. ranked  = H4_rank_intra_surface(primary)                     # references only; drop sub-top intents / tighten AMBIGUITY_DELTA\n59:   6. return base + ranked + overlay                               # overlay appended AFTER ranking, never ranked\n60: ```\n61: \n62: - **H1 re-key**: `RESOURCE_MAP[intent]` → `RESOURCE_MAP[surface][intent]` (`WEBFLOW`/`OPENCODE`) + a `UNIVERSAL` tier for `references/universal/*` so shared docs aren't duplicated across cells (keeps the drift-guard coverage check green without combinatorial blow-up).\n63: - **Asset deferral** (lowest-risk, highest single win): move all `assets/*` out of the first routed slice — zero scored-recall cost (no gold contains `assets/*`), removes SD-001's 5 checklists + recipe + 4 READMEs of pure scored-waste.\n64: - **H4**: ranks only the single-surface `primary`, references only; never the overlay, never a raw-count cap (recall is exact/all-or-nothing).\n65: \n66: ## 7. Regression Guard (REQ-003) — for the follow-on BUILD phase\n67: \n68: Run the deterministic `router-replay.cjs` + `score-skill-benchmark.cjs` harness over the **3 positive routing scenarios** (RD-002 excluded — negative advisor scenario, D3=0 is intended suppression). Gate the router change on ALL of:\n69: \n70: - **D2 per-scenario ≥ measured floor**: `SD-001 ≥ 0.727`, `LS-001 ≥ 1.0`, `CS-001 ≥ 0.60` (NOT 1.0 — it was never 1.0).\n71: - **D1-intra `surfaceMatch` stays `true`** on all three.\n72: - **CS-001 cross-surface recall**: all 4 `motion_dev/*` + the webflow implementation/verification gold refs remain routed (proves the overlay is full+unranked).\n73: - **Drift guard green**: `sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` — every routable `references/`/`assets/` doc reachable under ≥1 `(surface,intent)` or the `UNIVERSAL` cell; no orphaned doc.\n74: - **Target**: D3 rises from `{0.40, 0.312, 0.375}` toward `≥ 0.6` per scenario with no D2 floor breach.\n75: - **Sweep**: `AMBIGUITY_DELTA ∈ {0,1}` to confirm H4 ranking doesn't regress the legitimately multi-intent SD-001 (IMPLEMENTATION + ANIMATION, both gold-bearing).\n76: \n77: ## 8. Cross-surface Non-starvation Safeguard\n78: \n79: `crossSurface=true` fires when (a) the §2 mixed-marker case is detected (a task touching both surfaces, e.g. a `.opencode/` preview server shipping Webflow animation libs — OPENCODE wins the single pick but the Webflow half is still needed), OR (b) MOTION_DEV intent fires on a WEBFLOW route (the CS-001 class). On fire, append the **FULL, UNRANKED** secondary-surface intent slice (+ `MOTION_DEV_OVERLAY` on case b), after H4 ranking. Mandatory because CS-001's gold needs all 4 `motion_dev/*` refs and its D2 baseline is already only 0.60 — a capped overlay would breach the floor.\n80: \n81: ## 9. Honest Limits (REQ-004)\n82: \n83: - **D4 is n=2, single grader, \"approximate.\"** The \"routine hurts / domain helps\" claim rests on one scenario each. The *direction* is corroborated by the D3 cross-surface-waste evidence; the *magnitude* (0.13 / 0.10) is not a stable estimate. BUILD phase should add a synthetic third routine scenario before generalizing.\n84: - **Assets-scoring seam is real.** Deferring assets improves *scored* D3 at zero scored-recall cost, but the metric can't see a genuinely-useful checklist's value. Defer for the remediation; flag \"fold `expectedAssets` into scored gold\" as a separate benchmark-fidelity follow-on.\n85: - **D2 = 1.0 likely unreachable without a gold↔map reconciliation.** SD-001/CS-001 route gold paths absent from the fired intents' map slices (genuine recall misses) — a gold-authoring-vs-map-coverage mismatch H1/H4 can't close. Hence the baseline-floor guard.\n86: - **No post-fix D3 was executed** (research is charter-bound to no router edit). The actual post-fix number is the first thing the BUILD phase must verify live.\n87: \n88: ## 10. Handoff to the BUILD phase (open questions)\n89: \n90: 1. Run `routeSkillResources` against the surface-nested + reference-only + asset-deferred map; confirm D3 ≥ 0.6 with no D2 floor breach.\n\n(Showing lines 1-90 of 101. Use offset=91 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research — sk-code Routing-Efficiency & Usefulness Remediation\n\n> Synthesized from 3 native-Opus `@deep-research` iterations (converged at the planned stop). Source iterations: `iterations/iteration-00{1,2,3}.md`. Canonical findings ledger: `deltas/iter-00{1,2,3}.jsonl`.\n\n## 1. Question\n\nHow can `sk-code` load a tighter, task-appropriate resource slice that cuts **D3 over-routing** (live 42; routed ~16-20 vs gold ~5-8) and lifts **D4 routine-task usefulness** (≈49, task-dependent) **without regressing D1 routing or D2 discovery**?\n\n## 2. Convergence Report\n\n| Iteration | Focus | newInfoRatio | Outcome |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Root cause + structural H1/H2 | 0.70 | Root cause isolated; H1 = primary structural fix |\n| 2 | Dynamic H3/H4 + quantified frontier | 0.62 | H3 folds into H4; D2 was never 1.0; frontier quantified |\n| 3 | Synthesis + recommendation + guard | 0.18 | Ranked deliverable; converged |\n\nStop reason: **converged at the planned iteration 3** (all 4 hypotheses resolved, all 4 REQs answered).\n\n## 3. Root Cause (verified)\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/011-sk-code-routing-efficiency-remediation/research/research.md","time":{"start":1780372896857,"end":1780372896893}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b91e6a34f951fa7016a1e55a0c6bc819181926b40f2016e0f"}},"id":"prt_e867e7c360010oSs8tCGiI3aLE","sessionID":"ses_179821a7fffeliBzI3TOZnRjZf","messageID":"msg_e867e5478001iXymuwFIE4RAhB"}}
